{{zh-forms|[[车]][[同]][[轨]]，[[书]][[同]][[文]]|[[車同軌，書同文]]}}
==Chinese==
===Mandarin===
[[Pinyin]]: chē tóng guĭ, shū tóng wén
===Etymology===
In the Qin Dynasty, Emperor Qin Shihuang standardized the width of roads, and the writing system.  Today, this phrase refers generically to implementing universal standards.<br>
Literally: same ruts for carriages, same script for writing
===Idiom===
#  universal standards
#: ''[[微软]] Office 2003 [[新]][[成员]][[继]] OneNote [[之]][[后]]，[[昨天]][[再]][[发表]]Office InfoPath，[[展现]][[微软]][[在]][[信息]][[世界]][[中]]「'''车同轨，书同文'''」[[的]][[企图]]''[http://64.233.167.104/search?q=cache:Mwf4uk6ZJzEJ:www.oikos.com.tw/modules/news/article.php%3Fstoryid%3D1377+office+%22%E8%BD%A6%E5%90%8C%E8%BD%A8%EF%BC%8C%E4%B9%A6%E5%90%8C%E6%96%87%22&hl=zh-CN&gl=cn&ct=clnk&cd=4]
#: ''The newest member of [[Microsoft]] [[w:Microsoft Office|Office 2003]] follows on the heels of [[w:Microsoft Office OneNote|Microsoft OneNote]]; yesterday, [[w:Microsoft InfoPath|Office InfoPath]] was announced.  It displays [[Microsoft]]'s attempt to create "'''universal standards'''" for the information technology world''
